# Service folders, object folders & naming

Domain/business logic in this monorepo follows an fflib-style layout under [`apps/web/src/lib/`](apps/web/src/lib/). Always honor the folder + suffix conventions below when creating, moving, or renaming files. Tests live next to their source.

## What is a "service"

A service is **business / domain logic** scoped to one of our agents or to a cross-agent orchestrator. It coordinates Supabase queries, agent rules, relay publishes, etc. — anything that encodes domain behavior.

Things that are **not** services (do not place under `agents/`/`orchestrators/`, do not rename with `.service.ts`):

- Pure utilities, types, small helpers (e.g. `lib/automation-actor.ts`, `lib/format-usd-metric.ts`, `lib/trading/close-time-match.ts`).
- Integration clients / SDK wrappers (e.g. raw Bitvavo HTTP under `lib/bitvavo/`).
- UI / chart helpers (e.g. `lib/markets/chart-types.ts`, `aggregate-ohlcv.ts`, `fetch-market-chart-candles.ts`).
- Infra / cross-cutting: `lib/supabase/`, `lib/env/`, `lib/workers/`, `lib/relay/`, `lib/logs/`, `lib/locale/`, `lib/auth/`, `lib/dashboard/`, `lib/docs/`, `lib/ops/`, `lib/system-settings/`, `lib/tasks/`, `lib/catalog/`.

## Service location rules (always)

- **Single-namespace service** → `apps/web/src/lib/agents/<namespace>/services/<name>.service.ts`. Allowed namespaces (one per agent):
  - `ingest` — Bitvavo / CoinGecko sync, candle backfill windows, ingest schedulers.
  - `signal` — signal evaluators (MA cross / RSI / breakout-ATR), signal upsert / replay pipelines.
  - `trade-mediator` — catalog-close mediator pipelines.
  - `executor` — catalog-close executor pipelines, paper fills, executor rules / wallet / pnl, historical executor simulation.
- **Cross-namespace orchestrator** (combines ≥ 2 agents) → `apps/web/src/lib/orchestrators/<name>.service.ts`. No namespace folder.
- **Per-object service** (rare, scoped to one ObjectMetadata) → `apps/web/src/lib/objects/<object>/services/<name>.service.ts`. Create the `services/` subfolder only when the first service is added.

Never place agent-specific logic at the bare root of `lib/`, and never put orchestrators inside an agent namespace.

## Object location rules (always)

- One folder per object: `apps/web/src/lib/objects/<object>/<object>.object.ts` containing the `ObjectMetadata` subclass.
- Cross-cutting object files at the root: `lib/objects/registry.ts` (central `objectRegistry`) and `lib/objects/icons.ts` (icon registry).
- Import metadata types from `@adrikesteren/adricore/metadata`. Wire each new object class into `lib/objects/registry.ts`.

## Naming rules (always)

- Service files end in **`.service.ts`** (kebab-case, descriptive verb-ish name). Tests: `<name>.service.test.ts`.
- Object files end in **`.object.ts`** (kebab-case, matches its folder name). One class per file.
- Use **functional exports**: `export async function runFoo(...) { ... }`. No `class FooService` or `export const FooService = { ... }` wrappers (that may come later; not now).

## When in doubt

If a new file is borderline (e.g. could be a util or a service, or it touches two namespaces but feels like a helper), **ask the maintainer first** before creating it. Prefer a brief clarifying question over guessing the wrong folder.
